I think what you're talking about are template files. Like how you can include the same style sheet with a link element to use the same styling you want to use the same sidebar (X)HTML on all/most/certain pages, if I am correct.<br /><br />There are a few ways to do this. I use PHP and the code is rather simple...<br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold">index.php</span><br /><dl class="codebox"><dt>Code: </dt><dd><code>&lt;?php<br />include&#40;'sidebar.php'&#41;;<br />include&#40;'menu.php'&#41;;<br />?&gt;</code></dd></dl><br /><br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold">sidebar.php</span><br /><dl class="codebox"><dt>Code: </dt><dd><code>&lt;div id=&quot;side&quot;&gt;<br />&lt;p&gt;side bar here&lt;/p&gt;<br />&lt;/div&gt;<br />&lt;?php<br />// random PHP code intermixed if neccesary<br />?&gt;</code></dd></dl><br /><br />There is also SSI, Server Side Includes which uses Apache I think.<br /><br />If you're using a Microsoft server the code would look something like this...<br /><br /><dl class="codebox"><dt>Code: </dt><dd><code>&lt;!--#include virtual=&quot;header.html&quot;--&gt;</code></dd></dl><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="https://forums.whatwg.org/bb3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=47">JAB Creations</a> — Tue Mar 01, 2011 5:33 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
